1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 21=

3
00:01:41,711 --> 00:01:43,530
(Plagiarism is shameless!)
(Don't go around accusing people)

4
00:01:43,530 --> 00:01:44,450
(You plagiarized!?)
(of "borrowing ideas".)

5
00:01:44,450 --> 00:01:45,410
(Clout-chasing!)
(This isn't a tribute.)

6
00:01:45,410 --> 00:01:46,870
(Absurd! Boycott!)
(This is straight-up plagiarism.)

7
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:48,060
(I've followed this book for two years.)

8
00:01:48,060 --> 00:01:48,910
(He's not that kind of person.)

9
00:01:48,910 --> 00:01:49,760
(- I compared them.
- Mixing in other people's ideas)

10
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:51,240
(- Those are public elements.
- is not a free pass.)

11
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:52,070
(- This is worse than I thought.
- It's plagiarism.)

12
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,020
(It's an alternate account.)

13
00:01:53,020 --> 00:01:55,060
(Slapping a new skin on it
is even worse than copying it outright.)

14
00:01:55,060 --> 00:01:56,260
(If similar content means plagiarism,)

15
00:01:56,270 --> 00:01:58,160
(then no web novel should ever
be written anymore.)

16
00:02:06,020 --> 00:02:07,600
(Boycott Shattered Six States!
Boycott He Han!)

17
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:09,340
(I've supported you for years,
and you plagiarized?)

18
00:02:09,340 --> 00:02:12,780
(Shanghai Xintuo Fasteners Wholesale)

19
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:22,140
(Thanks.)

20
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,488
Did you see those comments
accusing you of borrowing ideas?

21
00:02:40,644 --> 00:02:42,400
Aren't you going to clear this up?

22
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:45,120
Lin Zhanqiao, can you stay out of this?

23
00:02:45,377 --> 00:02:47,320
Dai Shan's already
hounding me with questions.

24
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:48,400
Don't add fuel to the fire.

25
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,040
How am I adding fuel to the fire?

26
00:02:51,511 --> 00:02:53,560
Are you aware
that once public opinion takes off,

27
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,720
it can go either way?

28
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:56,960
If Mr. Fan sits back and watches,

29
00:02:56,977 --> 00:02:58,400
that's already being nice to you.

30
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,760
But if he starts fanning the flames

31
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:01,640
and this blows up,

32
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:03,320
it might even benefit the platform

33
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:04,600
with more traffic and attention.

34
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:05,440
But for you,

35
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:07,160
it'll definitely hurt you.

36
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,560
You know we can clarify this.

37
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,640
When you wrote Shattered Six States,

38
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:13,822
you were still with Chenxing.

39
00:03:13,888 --> 00:03:14,720
I was your editor.

40
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,240
So I have a responsibility

41
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,880
to step in and speak for you.

42
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:18,440
You don't.

43
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,160
And you're not my editor anymore.

44
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,920
What happens with this book

45
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,320
is between Dai Shan and me.

46
00:03:24,688 --> 00:03:26,288
You have no right to interfere.

47
00:03:49,477 --> 00:03:50,820
(Amy: So disappointed.
Followed this novel for so long.)

48
00:03:50,820 --> 00:03:53,020
(Source Code replies to Amy:
Exactly. Thought he was a great author.)

49
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,120
Someone suddenly pulls out

50
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,360
Parting Yan Dan at Yishui,

51
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,880
and tell mes it was written by
Phantom Knight five years ago.

52
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,720
Can't I also say he

53
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:19,920
or anyone wrote it after reading
Shattered Six States?

54
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:22,440
I'm here to discuss this,

55
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:22,840
right?

56
00:04:23,822 --> 00:04:25,240
You can't just say things like that.

57
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,480
The editor has all the emails.

58
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,000
There are timestamps on everything.

59
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:34,680
Of course.

60
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,280
It hasn't reached the level

61
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:38,320
of an IP dispute.

62
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:40,920
But there is public backlash now.

63
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,160
It's only right

64
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,333
that we prepare something.

65
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,880
An author's reputation matters, right?

66
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,560
Especially He Han's reputation.

67
00:04:48,644 --> 00:04:50,422
That's our top priority to protect.

68
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,360
How do you want to do?

69
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:56,120
You've noticed something off,

70
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:56,680
haven't you?

71
00:04:57,266 --> 00:04:59,080
That's exactly why
I wanted to talk to you.

72
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,480
He's on hiatus now, right?

73
00:05:00,577 --> 00:05:02,355
Let's just leave
what happened before this.

74
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,000
But if there's any more backlash,
do not respond.

75
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:07,480
Also, that part

76
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,960
about "turning back
and seeing him again",

77
00:05:10,066 --> 00:05:11,288
needs to be revised.

78
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:12,688
It has to be changed.

79
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:15,200
I'm worried it'll get blown out again.

80
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,177
Talk to him about it.

81
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,560
Honestly, I'm curious.

82
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,600
Just personally.

83
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,711
I didn't mean anything.

84
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:22,880
How did He Han

85
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:24,800
get access to Phantom Knight's

86
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:26,880
unpublished manuscript?

87
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:28,160
That's impossible.

88
00:05:28,577 --> 00:05:29,866
He couldn't have seen it.

89
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,440
He can be unreliable sometimes,

90
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,440
but not to the point

91
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,320
of risking everything over this.

92
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:42,320
This is the first time

93
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:44,680
I've seen you defend someone like this.

94
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,240
He Han has a lot of fans.

95
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,720
But he probably didn't expect

96
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:54,320
Phantom Knight's fans to be
several times more.

97
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:56,680
The author has disappeared for years,

98
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:58,900
(Plagiarism is unforgivable)
and the fans disappeared, too.

99
00:05:58,955 --> 00:06:00,630
(For real? Did you read it?)
Now that something has happened,

100
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:03,177
everyone suddenly realizes
how many people support that author.

101
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,080
I didn't expect

102
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,120
the current top spot
to be Phantom Knight.

103
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,800
An author who vanished for years

104
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:11,480
and an unfinished manuscript

105
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:12,777
still carry this much weight.

106
00:06:12,790 --> 00:06:14,300
Mr. Fan really knows what he's doing.

107
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,800
I even think

108
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:18,760
this whole mess

109
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,200
was orchestrated by him.

110
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,720
So He Han

111
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:25,720
is out of the sequel, right?

112
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:29,000
I think this is
actually a great move for you.

113
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,711
Lin Zhanqiao doesn't want me
to do the sequel.

114
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,640
What about you?

115
00:06:33,777 --> 00:06:35,044
Of course I want to write it.

116
00:06:35,088 --> 00:06:36,570
What if you write under a new pen name?

117
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,800
Will that be a problem?

118
00:06:38,111 --> 00:06:38,840
Chenxing and I...

119
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:39,640
I'm not signing you.

120
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:41,480
Who do you trust most?

121
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,444
I'll sign with them.

122
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:43,760
I'll handle Mr. Fan's side.

123
00:06:48,866 --> 00:06:50,622
Get back to me as soon as possible.

124
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:57,100
(Mengtong Internet Cafe)

125
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,280
Orange juice.

126
00:06:58,577 --> 00:06:59,240
Scan to pay.

127
00:07:00,660 --> 00:07:02,260
(I've supported you for years,
and you plagiarized?)

128
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:04,140
(Replies to Let's Dance: What proof
do you have that He Han plagiarized?)

129
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:09,060
(Don't sway public opinion!
He didn't plagiarize!)

130
00:07:13,577 --> 00:07:14,800
Why aren't the lights on?

131
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:16,760
Ms. Lin,

132
00:07:17,266 --> 00:07:18,640
Mr. He Han is getting attacked.

133
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:19,920
I'm trying to defend him.

134
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:22,360
But Phantom Knight's fans are too many.

135
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,555
I can't keep up with them.

136
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,440
How can you fight

137
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,120
that many people alone?

138
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,640
I know I can't win,

139
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,440
but I just can't stay quiet.

140
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,911
How can they say things like that
about Mr. He Han?

141
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:36,000
Plagiarism and clout-chasing?

142
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:38,040
It's making me pissed off!

143
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:38,640
Alright.

144
00:07:38,711 --> 00:07:40,911
Whoever insults Mr. He Han,
I'll fire back at all of them.

145
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,760
It's late. You haven't eaten, right?

146
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:44,190
Let's go.

147
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:44,690
I can't eat.

148
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,155
Alright. Calm down. Come on.

149
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,160
Look at this profile picture.

150
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:48,360
You can tell
they're not a decent person!

151
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,200
Yeah, I know.

152
00:07:49,210 --> 00:07:50,320
They're just asking to be roasted.

153
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:51,640
He'll handle it himself.

154
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,160
One statement from him

155
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:55,240
is more effective
than you typing all night.

156
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,120
But he hasn't said anything.

157
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,120
Something happened to him recently.

158
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:04,760
And with this mess now,

159
00:08:04,822 --> 00:08:07,066
he probably doesn't have the mood
to respond.

160
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,560
Has he contacted you?

161
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,120
I've tried reaching out to him,

162
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,600
but he screens my calls and texts.

163
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,160
That just proves

164
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,600
he's in a really bad state right now.

165
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,240
I'm honestly scared

166
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,040
he might stop writing because of this.

167
00:08:23,888 --> 00:08:25,511
There are only a few days left

168
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,520
of his one-week break.

169
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:28,840
Fans arguing with each other is normal.

170
00:08:29,288 --> 00:08:30,320
It'll calm down soon.

171
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,560
It's not that simple.

172
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,400
Phantom Knight's fans

173
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:34,920
have started boycotting He Han

174
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:36,080
and Shattered Six States.

175
00:08:37,040 --> 00:08:38,160
The streaming platform bought

176
00:08:38,160 --> 00:08:39,933
the TV adaptation
of Shattered Six States,

177
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,600
and now those fans

178
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,560
are boycotting

179
00:08:42,560 --> 00:08:44,000
the drama, too.

180
00:08:44,422 --> 00:08:45,777
Why do they get to do that?

181
00:08:49,955 --> 00:08:51,000
Fuel up on orange juice,

182
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,280
and let's keep going.

183
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,880
The platform's legal team called.

184
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:03,600
They said the authorization details
for Shattered Six States

185
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:06,920
might need to be renegotiated.

186
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:10,920
Don't sell it to them.

187
00:09:11,244 --> 00:09:13,066
It's not like they're the only buyer.

188
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,880
I don't think it's a big deal.

189
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,960
They probably just want to wait
until the novel is nearly finished

190
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,240
and the controversy dies down

191
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,400
before paying the rest.

192
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,280
Honestly,

193
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,240
their offer is still pretty high.

194
00:09:29,644 --> 00:09:31,400
As long as they don't cut the price,

195
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:33,320
we can make

196
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,560
some small concessions.

197
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:35,480
I'll leave it to you.

198
00:09:46,680 --> 00:09:47,840
Don't read the comments.

199
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:49,044
It'll mess with your mood.

200
00:09:49,288 --> 00:09:50,360
It's not that serious.

201
00:09:50,622 --> 00:09:53,640
It's not like this is my first day
writing web novels. I've heard worse.

202
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:56,080
At most, they'll call me a plagiarist,

203
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,266
say I've run out of ideas.

204
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,040
I've done nothing wrong.

205
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,720
Can you not reply to the comments?

206
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,280
I won't.

207
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:07,000
Don't worry.

208
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,155
You should head back early.

209
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:25,600
You've got two days
before your update resumes.

210
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:26,720
I know.

211
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:30,680
I'll get going then.

212
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:37,680
Let's talk in my room.

213
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:11,880
Are you okay?

214
00:12:15,177 --> 00:12:16,822
Why did you come all the way here?

215
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:20,640
Because you refused to see me.

216
00:12:21,044 --> 00:12:22,644
I had no choice but to come here.

217
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:25,400
I was working on a case.

218
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,760
It's a very tricky one.

219
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:31,040
I didn't have a single moment free
until tonight.

220
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:33,640
See?

221
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,520
I came straight to you

222
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:36,840
right after I finished.

223
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:40,240
Even if you hadn't come
to Yichun tonight,

224
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:41,960
I would've gone to Shanghai

225
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:43,680
to find you tomorrow.

226
00:12:44,380 --> 00:12:46,140
(New Recording)

227
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,080
You know

228
00:12:51,933 --> 00:12:54,400
I came to see you about
the company under my name, right?

229
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:57,000
You're the one in control of it.

230
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,840
Now the company's in trouble.

231
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:01,480
There are things

232
00:13:02,133 --> 00:13:02,960
I need to ask you.

233
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,320
Turn off the recording.

234
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,200
Did Zhang Yousen tell you to do this?

235
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:26,911
Is he here, too?

236
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,720
Your young boyfriend

237
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:33,440
thinks too simply.

238
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:42,200
Fine.

239
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:44,880
If you want to record, go ahead.

240
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,760
I know what you want to ask.

241
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:49,720
I'll keep it simple.

242
00:13:51,111 --> 00:13:52,520
The six million plus in unpaid taxes

243
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,920
under your company's name

244
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,040
will be covered by me.

245
00:13:57,688 --> 00:13:59,044
You don't need to worry.

246
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:00,160
As for this company,

247
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,840
you can keep it or shut it down.

248
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,560
That's up to you.

249
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:07,560
Tell Zhang Yousen

250
00:14:07,777 --> 00:14:09,240
he doesn't need to rack his brain,

251
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:11,288
trying to come up with
a perfect solution for you.

252
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,960
From the first day I met you,

253
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,720
I decided that nothing

254
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,520
would ever hurt you

255
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:21,520
or let you feel upset.

256
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:37,640
How do I know you're telling the truth?

257
00:14:41,466 --> 00:14:42,960
When you get to Shanghai tomorrow,

258
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,360
your finance team will tell you

259
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,360
all the taxes have been paid.

260
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:49,960
This isn't

261
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:52,480
a small amount of money.

262
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,000
Whether it's a lot or a little,
that's my problem.

263
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,040
I'll handle it.

264
00:14:56,644 --> 00:14:58,600
You shouldn't have to worry
about this anymore.

265
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:03,280
Six million plus

266
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:06,840
with late fees,
it's around seven million.

267
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,760
Can you come up with that much

268
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:12,120
at once?

269
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:19,480
Are you worried about me?

270
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:28,960
I just don't want you to rob Peter

271
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:30,960
to pay Paul.

272
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:31,960
No.

273
00:15:32,777 --> 00:15:33,720
Aside from this company

274
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:34,960
I'm working with you,

275
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,355
I don't have anything else anymore.

276
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:52,920
There is something

277
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:55,280
I need to tell you.

278
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,040
I've told my wife

279
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:00,880
everything.

280
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,880
She's going to help me cover this money.

281
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:14,840
What do you mean?

282
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:18,960
She knows the company is under my name?

283
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:22,640
Yes.

284
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:27,480
I told her

285
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:30,200
I set it up

286
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:33,480
for work and financial dealings.

287
00:16:38,088 --> 00:16:39,160
Does she believe you?

288
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:41,266
Whether she believes it or not
doesn't matter.

289
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:44,080
What matters is that I've promised her

290
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:47,280
that from now on,

291
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,000
we'll draw a clear line.

292
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:53,880
There'll be

293
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:56,960
no more contact.

294
00:16:58,280 --> 00:16:59,360
You and the company?

295
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:02,960
The company

296
00:17:05,320 --> 00:17:06,040
and you.

297
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:44,120
You say no more contact.

298
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:49,560
Will I still be able to see you?

299
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:29,040
You deserve a better man

300
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:31,640
and life.

301
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:50,660
(How did the talk go?)

302
00:18:51,580 --> 00:18:54,020
(Zhang Yousen: How did the talk go?)

303
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:05,250
♪If the sky and the sea traded places♪

304
00:19:07,270 --> 00:19:12,840
♪If a fish fell in love with a bird♪

305
00:19:14,780 --> 00:19:21,390
♪If we hadn't wavered♪

306
00:19:21,444 --> 00:19:22,720
You shouldn't have come here.

307
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:26,340
♪We wouldn't have lost each other
in the crowd♪

308
00:19:26,340 --> 00:19:27,622
I really shouldn't have come.

309
00:19:29,450 --> 00:19:31,710
♪We met in the thirteenth month♪

310
00:19:31,710 --> 00:19:33,570
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

311
00:19:33,570 --> 00:19:35,950
♪And found our way back whole♪

312
00:19:36,930 --> 00:19:39,120
♪Let love surge like raging waves♪

313
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:43,520
♪Crashing over us, never fading♪

314
00:19:44,390 --> 00:19:47,700
♪Even if we're drenched in the rain♪

315
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:51,290
♪Even if time buries us away♪

316
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:54,320
♪At least we still have♪

317
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:58,860
♪This one eternal photo♪

318
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:04,560
♪Let's not lose each other again♪

319
00:20:05,010 --> 00:20:08,410
♪People only realize what matters
after losing it♪

320
00:20:08,910 --> 00:20:11,190
♪In another time and space♪

321
00:20:11,190 --> 00:20:15,390
♪We'll grow old together♪

322
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:21,190
♪But the sky can never trade places
with the sea♪

323
00:20:24,130 --> 00:20:32,970
♪And a fish will never fall in love
with a bird♪

324
00:20:34,620 --> 00:20:35,960
(Rukawa Kaeda: Plagiarist! Get lost!
Refund!)

325
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:38,000
(Zhanzhu replies to Rukawa Kaeda:
He did not plagiarize!)

326
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,180
(He took the photo of you, didn't he?)

327
00:20:39,180 --> 00:20:40,820
(The big fan is losing it
before the author even says a word.)

328
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,160
What's wrong?

329
00:20:58,720 --> 00:20:59,520
Didn't I tell you

330
00:20:59,520 --> 00:21:00,720
not to argue with them?

331
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:01,800
You can't win against them.

332
00:21:03,222 --> 00:21:04,320
Alright. That's enough.

333
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,160
Let me see.

334
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,280
They're piling on you online.

335
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:25,920
These are edited, right?

336
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,440
I don't know how they got them.

337
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:34,800
That is my face,

338
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:36,840
but I've never worn those clothes.

339
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:40,440
They...

340
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:43,000
They're saying

341
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:48,360
I'm that kind of person.

342
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:51,160
They're asking how much
Mr. He Han paid me.

343
00:21:55,288 --> 00:21:56,688
I'll report this to the police

344
00:21:56,711 --> 00:21:58,311
and file a complaint with the platform.

345
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:17,640
Can you not reply to the comments?

346
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:39,320
(Replies to "Photoshopped or a boob job?
Might as well invest in a brain".)

347
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:40,860
(People can really be this confident.
Is it ignorance?)

348
00:23:40,860 --> 00:23:41,820
(Living up to your username!)

349
00:23:41,820 --> 00:23:43,830
(Replies to Rukawa Kaeda:
Did he tell you that in bed?)

350
00:23:43,844 --> 00:23:45,780
(Come to my bed, I'll tell you myself!)

351
00:23:45,780 --> 00:23:46,660
(Melon Thief Critter:
What gives you the right)

352
00:23:46,660 --> 00:23:47,500
(to prove He Han innocent
by typing a few words?)

353
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:48,560
(What's your relationship with him?
He hasn't even said anything.)

354
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:49,720
(Replies to Melon Thief Critter:
Here's my advice: Get offline for now.)

355
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:50,940
(What you need to do is jump into
a pot with cabbage and vermicelli.)

356
00:23:54,660 --> 00:23:57,140
(He Han replies to Rukawa Kaeda:
Come to my bed, I'll tell you myself!)

357
00:23:57,140 --> 00:23:58,100
(Zhangzhu replies:
You don't read any of his work.)

358
00:23:58,100 --> 00:24:00,140
(He Han replies to Melon Thief Critter:
Here's my advice: Get offline for now)

359
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:01,320
(What you need to do is jump into
a pot with cabbage and vermicelli.)

360
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:15,400
Ms. Lin.

361
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:17,880
Ms. Lin.

362
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:21,280
Ms. Lin.

363
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:23,000
Mr. He Han replied.

364
00:24:23,577 --> 00:24:24,600
Look at this.

365
00:24:28,320 --> 00:24:29,040
He's done for.

366
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:31,640
What are you guys doing?

367
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:56,240
Say no more.

368
00:24:57,555 --> 00:24:59,400
I know I shouldn't have replied to
those trolls.

369
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:00,822
But I really couldn't hold it in.

370
00:25:01,066 --> 00:25:02,740
They can say
whatever they want about me.

371
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:03,920
But smearing and attacking

372
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:05,520
a young girl like that

373
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:06,720
is disgusting.

374
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:07,880
Did you see those photos?

375
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:10,160
I can't just watch my readers

376
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:11,440
take the hits for me

377
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:13,244
while I hide behind them and
sit on my hands.

378
00:25:14,577 --> 00:25:16,888
Don't worry. I won't let things
get out of hand.

379
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:27,880
Listen to me.

380
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:30,040
No more posting.

381
00:25:30,050 --> 00:25:31,120
I want to help Mr. He Han.

382
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:32,440
We all do.

383
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:33,640
But not in this way.

384
00:25:50,740 --> 00:25:58,700
(Recipient: Ma,
Subject: Statement on Phantom Knight)

385
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:55,000
Lawyer Bei has left.

386
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:57,080
I've broken up with him.

387
00:26:57,840 --> 00:26:59,000
We were both wrong.

388
00:26:59,177 --> 00:27:01,240
He'll take responsibility
for the company's debt.

389
00:27:01,333 --> 00:27:03,444
I didn't realize
you loved him that much!

390
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:05,520
So we should break up as well.

391
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:07,288
But I don't want to break up with you.

392
00:27:11,111 --> 00:27:13,160
You and I were
never really in a relationship.

393
00:27:13,533 --> 00:27:15,222
That's because
Lawyer Bei was around before.

394
00:27:15,230 --> 00:27:16,933
Not that he's gone.
It's a good thing for me.

395
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:18,560
But I won't love anyone again.

396
00:27:18,755 --> 00:27:19,933
That's not necessarily true.

397
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:21,720
I can prove it to you.

398
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:37,320
You've seen it?

399
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:40,520
Happy?

400
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:44,640
Why would I be happy?

401
00:27:44,920 --> 00:27:46,800
I don't want any of you to get hurt.

402
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:49,400
I care about how Dingqi does,

403
00:27:49,466 --> 00:27:51,888
and I care just as much about
whether you win or lose.

404
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:53,360
The streaming platform wants to

405
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:57,160
renegotiate the contract.

406
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:00,840
They want a price cut, right?

407
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:02,520
How much?

408
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:07,880
Half.

409
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:14,680
That's tricky.

410
00:28:14,733 --> 00:28:16,955
You already secured
Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui.

411
00:28:17,080 --> 00:28:19,000
Can't you contact Phantom Knight?

412
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:21,800
We have only talked to Ma.

413
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,000
Phantom Knight's agent.

414
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:24,680
This person is overseas now.

415
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:26,160
So you're saying

416
00:28:26,160 --> 00:28:27,720
only Ma

417
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:30,040
can reach Phantom Knight?

418
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:30,520
Yes.

419
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:33,560
Don't expect the agent
to reveal anything.

420
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:34,360
And this time,

421
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:35,520
don't expect him

422
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:37,800
to bring Phantom Knight out either.

423
00:28:47,620 --> 00:28:50,220
(Luo Jingjing)

424
00:28:52,755 --> 00:28:54,890
The sequel contract
for Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui

425
00:28:54,911 --> 00:28:55,733
has been signed.

426
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:57,920
The news should be out soon.

427
00:29:00,577 --> 00:29:02,000
Who did you get to write it?

428
00:29:03,280 --> 00:29:03,760
A newbie.

429
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:06,600
Fan, what exactly

430
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:08,440
are you up to?

431
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:09,760
By the way,

432
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:13,200
I don't want

433
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,555
Lin Zhanqiao's company anymore.

434
00:29:23,740 --> 00:29:25,460
(New author Sansan continues
the legend of Phantom Knight!)

435
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:26,680
Who's Sansan?

436
00:29:26,733 --> 00:29:28,066
Zhao Lanxin found this person.

437
00:29:28,080 --> 00:29:28,680
No idea.

438
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:30,320
The update drops tonight.

439
00:29:30,800 --> 00:29:32,000
We'll see what Sansan has got.

440
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:34,840
I don't remember any of the newcomers
she poached from us

441
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,240
called Sansan.

442
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:38,160
I think Sansan's a girl.

443
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:39,400
Hard to say.

444
00:29:43,733 --> 00:29:46,310
This is the first time
we're working with an author like this.

445
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,720
It shows

446
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:48,800
we trust each other enough.

447
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:51,280
Did you read what I sent?

448
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:51,960
Yeah.

449
00:29:52,022 --> 00:29:53,155
The editor read it, too.

450
00:29:53,360 --> 00:29:54,320
You're a genius.

451
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:57,120
Tonight, everyone will see

452
00:29:57,120 --> 00:29:58,040
a new author, Sansan,

453
00:29:58,240 --> 00:29:59,280
come into the spotlight.

454
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:02,120
I'm starting to understand

455
00:30:02,280 --> 00:30:03,520
how Phantom Knight felt.

456
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:06,760
Famous name

457
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:08,320
and no face.

458
00:30:10,888 --> 00:30:11,977
It's kind of thrilling.

459
00:30:13,260 --> 00:30:16,780
(Ma: Copyright regarding Phantom Knight
and Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

460
00:30:17,780 --> 00:30:21,260
(Phantom Knight
and Parting with Yan Dan at Yishui)

461
00:30:32,888 --> 00:30:35,644
Sir, would you like gold-filled
engraving and an incense burner?

462
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:38,040
No.

463
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:38,880
Alright.

464
00:30:39,480 --> 00:30:39,840
Let's go.

465
00:30:47,500 --> 00:30:49,940
(Grave of Late Father, He Wei)

466
00:30:49,940 --> 00:30:52,740
(Guizhou Moutai)

467
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:05,560
Why did you pick
such a nice spot for him?

468
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:18,680
No need to do all that.

469
00:31:18,690 --> 00:31:20,933
He wouldn't care.
As long as there's alcohol, he's fine.

470
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:23,560
You think he doesn't care,

471
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:26,320
but I think he cares a lot.

472
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:38,040
Now he can drink as much as he wants.

473
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:44,880
Give him a toast.

474
00:31:56,577 --> 00:31:58,720
You two are the worst father and son
I've ever seen.

475
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:03,080
At least now, you're both free.

476
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:05,560
He Wei.

477
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:07,800
He Han.

478
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:10,680
Both are free.

479
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:18,960
To be honest, I kind of miss him.

480
00:32:20,044 --> 00:32:21,160
It's not what you think.

481
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:24,560
It's just that back then,

482
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,640
he was my excuse for being a mess.

483
00:32:32,088 --> 00:32:33,266
Now that he's gone,

484
00:32:35,022 --> 00:32:36,120
that excuse is gone, too.

485
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:07,040
Dad.

486
00:33:17,720 --> 00:33:18,640
This is my last drink.

487
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:21,480
From today on,

488
00:33:22,555 --> 00:33:23,444
I'm quitting.

489
00:33:57,680 --> 00:33:59,080
How are you going to do

490
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,120
with those trolls?

491
00:34:02,955 --> 00:34:03,920
I leave it to Dai Shan.

492
00:34:05,355 --> 00:34:07,666
She doesn't know the truth
about Phantom Knight.

493
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:11,280
No one does.

494
00:34:15,560 --> 00:34:16,960
I emailed Ma yesterday.

495
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:18,360
I wanted to see

496
00:34:18,511 --> 00:34:20,577
if he would come out and say something.

497
00:34:21,240 --> 00:34:22,160
He replied.

498
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:23,480
He said

499
00:34:23,640 --> 00:34:25,120
he didn't think things through

500
00:34:25,240 --> 00:34:26,720
when he sold the rights.

501
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:28,960
So he's willing

502
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:30,480
to step in

503
00:34:30,520 --> 00:34:31,880
as the current rights holder

504
00:34:31,911 --> 00:34:33,488
and the former editor to mediate.

505
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:34,640
That won't help.

506
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:37,160
It's just a hollow official statement.

507
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:38,360
I know.

508
00:34:39,720 --> 00:34:41,360
But that's our only option now.

509
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:44,160
Unless...

510
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:46,360
we reveal

511
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:47,720
Phantom Knight's identity.

512
00:34:50,440 --> 00:34:51,360
Don't be ridiculous.

513
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:54,400
This isn't life or death.

514
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,760
It's just a novel.

515
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:59,360
Phantom Knight appeals to the public

516
00:34:59,360 --> 00:35:01,240
because of his mysterious identity.

517
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:02,920
If you reveal his identity,

518
00:35:02,920 --> 00:35:03,880
what's left?

519
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,760
If this keeps blowing up online,

520
00:35:07,120 --> 00:35:08,080
I'm worried it'll hurt

521
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:09,640
your reputation in the industry.

522
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:10,840
I'll handle it myself.

523
00:35:11,977 --> 00:35:13,333
This has nothing to do with you

524
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:14,920
or Phantom Knight.

525
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:50,440
Where were you last night?

526
00:35:56,533 --> 00:35:57,600
I went on a business trip.

527
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:58,560
Where to?

528
00:35:59,520 --> 00:35:59,960
Yichun.

529
00:36:01,711 --> 00:36:03,088
Which hotel did you stay at?

530
00:36:08,520 --> 00:36:09,360
Xinggui Hotel.

531
00:36:09,640 --> 00:36:11,200
Why did you do your hair?

532
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:13,760
And you came back wearing high heels.

533
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:16,320
Work event.

534
00:36:18,920 --> 00:36:20,600
What about all these?

535
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:22,760
Did you buy this much makeup

536
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:24,320
also for a work event?

537
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:27,720
No.

538
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:31,080
You bought these for yourself?

539
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:36,520
What are you trying to do?

540
00:36:36,720 --> 00:36:37,600
Nothing.

541
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:41,600
I just want to look better.

542
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:44,080
Your natural look is already the best.

543
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:46,960
You don't need makeup to cover anything.

544
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:12,400
You can throw the rest away.

545
00:37:12,533 --> 00:37:13,640
These two are expensive.

546
00:37:14,333 --> 00:37:15,400
I'll keep them.

547
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:17,040
Where did you get the nerve

548
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:19,520
to go against me?

549
00:37:20,520 --> 00:37:21,360
Which man is it?

550
